WHO   — Ilyusha & the Boys — Hurrah for Karamazov
WHAT  — The final, hopeful note: at Ilyusha's funeral Alyosha tells the boys that one good memory from childhood may someday save them, and they cry ‘Hurrah for Karamazov!’
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because after the murder, the trial, and the devil, Dostoevsky ends not on despair but on children, memory, and love — the future of the answer.
HOW   — By a vow among boys to be good and to remember, led by Alyosha at the graveside.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  One good memory, kept from childhood, may be the very thing that saves a man — so remember, and be kind, and: Hurrah for Karamazov!

